National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice visited Islamabad, Pakistan to meet with Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, Advisor to the Prime Minister on National Security and Foreign Affairs Sartaj Aziz, Chief of Army Staff General Raheel Sharif, and other officials. They discussed ways to strengthen the relationship between the United States and Pakistan and work together on regional and global issues. Rice praised Pakistan's support for talks between the Afghan government and the Taliban and urged them to intensify efforts to counter terrorist sanctuaries within its borders. She also invited Prime Minister Sharif to visit the White House in October 2015 to further strengthen the US-Pakistani relationship. Rice also met with civil society leaders and expressed support for their work in promoting human rights, development, and civil liberties in Pakistan.